Process Solutions?<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#banks-that-provide-payment-cards\" title=\"Banks that provide Payment Cards\">Banks that provide Payment Cards<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#the-acquiring-or-receiving-bank\" title=\"The Acquiring or Receiving Bank\">The Acquiring or Receiving Bank<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#card-networks\" title=\"Card Networks\">Card Networks<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#the-merchants-payment-processors\" title=\"The Merchant\u2019s Payment Processors\">The Merchant\u2019s Payment Processors<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#the-independent-sales-organization\" title=\"The Independent Sales Organization\">The Independent Sales Organization<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#the-card-payment-facilitators\" title=\"The Card Payment Facilitators\">The Card Payment Facilitators<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#how-has-the-payment-landscape-changed-to-offer-simplified-payment-processes\" title=\"How has the Payment Landscape changed to offer Simplified Payment Processes?\">How has the Payment Landscape changed to offer Simplified Payment Processes?<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3'><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#the-upcoming-of-several-fintech-companies\" title=\"The Upcoming of Several Fintech Companies\">The Upcoming of Several Fintech Companies<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#the-emergence-of-new-payment-methods\" title=\"The Emergence of New Payment Methods\">The Emergence of New Payment Methods<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-14\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#an-increase-in-eft-payment-solutions\" title=\"An Increase in EFT Payment Solutions\">An Increase in EFT Payment Solutions<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-15\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#a-reduction-in-the-use-of-paper-money\" title=\"A Reduction in the use of Paper Money\">A Reduction in the use of Paper Money<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-16\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/simplifying-the-complexity-of-payments\/#choosing-the-right-payment-process-solutions\" title=\"Choosing the Right Payment Process Solutions\">Choosing the Right Payment Process Solutions<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-causes-the-complexity-of-payments\"><\/span>What causes the Complexity of Payments?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The payment ecosystem comprises several parts, which make it complex. When a customer initiates a transaction, for example, by swiping a bank card at the payment terminal, the process may take a few seconds. However, the process involves the interactions of several players.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the players include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Companies that facilitate the transaction process<\/li><li>Service providers that offer the services to the merchants<\/li><li>Banks that have the business\u2019 account<\/li><li>Banks that offer credit cards to customers<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The payment system undergoes two main processes that include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-authorization-procedure\"><\/span>The Authorization Procedure<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The authorization process involves a series of processes that involve:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The customer initiates the <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-multiple-payment-gateways-help-merchants-sell\/#:~:text=Anyone%20looking%20to%20expand%20their%20business%20to%20a%20global%20scale%20should%20consider%20whether%20their%20current%20payment%20provider%20can%20handle%20such%20a%20shift.\">payment process<\/a> by swiping a debit or credit card at the point of sale terminal<\/li><li>The payment processor receives the card information. It then passes the information and the amount to the merchant\u2019s bank.<\/li><li>Once the bank receives the information, it forwards the payment request to the customer\u2019s card network.<\/li><li>The card\u2019s system routes the transaction and a request for approval. Approval or decline depends on whether the funds in the customer\u2019s account are sufficient.<\/li><li>The issuing bank transfers the response to the card network. In case of approval, the bank assigns and transfers an authorization code.<\/li><li>The acquiring bank receives the authorization code sent from the card association.<\/li><li>The credit card network sends the approval to the acquiring bank through the payment processor.<\/li><li>The merchant\u2019s bank routes the approval code to the payment processor, which prints a receipt to finalize the process.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-settlement-procedure\"><\/span>The Settlement Procedure<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The merchant transmits all the payment information to the payment processor at the end of the day. The processor then transmits all the information to the receiving bank. This process is known as capture. Once it is complete, the receiving bank transfers the card information to the card network then completes the approved transactions to the payer\u2019s bank. The issuing bank sends the money to the receiving bank and is deposited in the merchant\u2019s account.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/key-players-in-payments.jpg\" alt=\"key players in payments\" class=\"wp-image-818\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/key-players-in-payments.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/key-players-in-payments-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/key-players-in-payments-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"who-are-the-key-players-in-payment-process-solutions\"><\/span>Who are the Key Players in Payment Process Solutions?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"banks-that-provide-payment-cards\"><\/span>Banks that provide Payment Cards<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These banks can also be referred to as the issuer. They provide customers with credit cards on behalf of the card network company. They are also responsible for making payments on behalf of the customer. In a credit card, the issuing bank assumes the risks of an inability to pay for the card balance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-acquiring-or-receiving-bank\"><\/span>The Acquiring or Receiving Bank<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The receiving bank or acquirer is the bank that allows merchants to accept different forms of card payments from any client. The acquiring bank\u2019s main purpose is to process the card payment on behalf of the merchant.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/\">Verv<\/a> is a good example of an acquiring bank that acts as a payment processor. It takes the merchant risks by transferring payment information to the card network to complete the payment.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"card-networks\"><\/span>Card Networks<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Several <a href=\"https:\/\/www.businessinsider.com\/credit-card-networks-payment-list?r=US&amp;IR=T\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">card networks<\/a> exist in the market today. These card networks facilitate all the transactions between the consumer, the merchant, and the banks. They are responsible for monitoring and overseeing the processing while regulating their card network\u2019s management.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The service providers issue electronic networks that allow the different parties to communicate and perform transactions. These companies charge for the services they offer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-merchants-payment-processors\"><\/span>The Merchant\u2019s Payment Processors<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Some people refer to it as merchant service providers. These major companies offer payment services to merchants. Their main role is to offer merchant accounts, accept card payments, and offer protection against fraud.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most payment processors are linked to the acquiring bank. Two types of payment processors exist in the market. These include;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Front-end processors<\/li><li>Back-end processors<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The front-end processors channel the payments made at the merchant to the cardholder\u2019s bank to initiate an authorization request. On the other hand, the backend processors accept the settlement terms and transfer the payment to the issuing bank.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-independent-sales-organization\"><\/span>The Independent Sales Organization<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The ISO comprises companies that manufacture and sell card processing services to merchants. These companies act as intermediaries between the merchants, acquiring banks and payment processors. Some ISOs are banks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-card-payment-facilitators\"><\/span>The Card Payment Facilitators<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Payment facilitators are ISOs that work as bigger merchant processing accounts. It controls numerous small sub-merchants under one umbrella. This business plan allows the facilitators to provide merchants with seamless and instantaneous onboarding processes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"how-has-the-payment-landscape-changed-to-offer-simplified-payment-processes\"><\/span>How has the Payment Landscape changed to offer Simplified Payment Processes?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-upcoming-of-several-fintech-companies\"><\/span>The Upcoming of Several Fintech Companies<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Technology giants are slowly dominating the payment industry. Conventional payment providers such as banks are now merging with technological companies to keep their customers close. Different partnerships and acquisitions have taken place in the past few years.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These partnerships allow merchants to provide a seamless payment channel that enhances customer experience. A <a href=\"https:\/\/www.jdpower.com\/business\/press-releases\/2021-us-banking-and-credit-card-mobile-app-satisfaction-studies\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">recent study<\/a> shows that banking apps saw a 15% drop since most clients found them hard to use. Therefore, fintech companies provide efficient systems with customer-friendly solutions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"the-emergence-of-new-payment-methods\"><\/span>The Emergence of New Payment Methods<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The widespread use of smartphones has led to mobile wallet apps. The increase in mobile wallets has made merchants acquire mobile point-of-sale solutions that accept payments from these mobile wallets, contactless payments, and digital native products such as <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/technology\/\">Verv products<\/a> that attract the younger generation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"an-increase-in-eft-payment-solutions\"><\/span>An Increase in EFT Payment Solutions<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/electronic-funds-transfer-benefits-security-cost\/\">Electronic Fund Transfer<\/a> is a broad term that encompasses the movement of funds electronically over a network. These transactions do not involve any paperwork, and they include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Direct bank deposits<\/li><li>E-checks<\/li><li>ATM withdrawals<\/li><li>Wire transfer<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>EFTs provide a convenient and easy way to process payments after purchasing goods. This payment channel is growing popular, especially with peer-to-peer apps. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/advisor\/banking\/what-are-ach-payments-and-how-they-work\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ACH transfers<\/a> help pay recurring bills such as electricity, entertainment, and other utilities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"a-reduction-in-the-use-of-paper-money\"><\/span>A Reduction in the use of Paper Money<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Although some people still use cash to pay for goods, the total number of people using cash has reduced. Many people adopt digital payment channels such as online shopping, card transactions, and peer-to-peer apps.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, merchants encourage their customers to pay using digital forms. It helps businesses reduce the amount of money at their business premises and minimizes frequent trips to the bank. A <a href=\"https:\/\/www.csis.org\/analysis\/developing-inclusive-digital-payment-systems\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">recent study<\/a> in the U.S established that digital payments account for more than $961 million and are estimated to reach $1.3 billion in 2023.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"choosing-the-right-payment-process-solutions\"><\/span>Choosing the Right Payment Process Solutions<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Despite the complexity of payments, the financial industry is a broad landscape influenced by innovation. The ability of the financial industry to provide simplified payment processes enabled the growth of investments and led to increased partnerships and acquisitions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>New companies such as Verv are some of the best fintech companies that offer banking as a service in the field. The company aims at changing the overall payment landscape by providing solutions to ease the complexity of payments. Join them by visiting their official website, where you will enjoy seamless and simplified payment processes.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The article below describes the complexity of payments and detailed information on simplified payment processes.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":817,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"templa